  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are in active hedging mode as SPX broke below the 6541 GEX flip into negative gamma territory, forcing them to sell the break and amplify downside momentum toward the massive -7768M gamma wall at 6500. The PIN regime's mean-reversion characteristics are currently overwhelmed by the wall break event, with dealers likely dumping delta as spot approaches 6500 where they'll turn into aggressive buyers. \n\nWatch for violent snap-back once 6500 holds as dealers flip from selling pressure to buying support, with upside capped by the dense positive gamma cluster between 6530-6550 that will create selling resistance on any bounce.",
